  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0db9\u0dd4\u0da7\u0db1\u0dca \u0d87\u0da7\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dd3 \u0daf\u0dc3 \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd2 \u0daf\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0db8\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A ten-year-old child died after getting stuck in a rambutan bone",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the Kankasanturaya police, a ten-year-old child who was admitted to Thelippalai Hospital, Jaffna, died after a rambutan seed got stuck in his throat.",
        "While eating the rambutan that was brought home, the rambutan seed got stuck in the child's throat and due to difficulty in breathing, the parents took the child to Thelippalai Hospital and died.",
        "The police said that the deceased was a ten-year-old boy named Dharmarasa Darshikan, a resident of Kollankalandi, Kankasanturaya, Jaffna.",
        "The child was eating rambutan when a rambutan seed got stuck and the child's parents, who did not know that a rambutan seed was stuck in his throat, took him to the hospital thinking it was an illness, police said.",
        "A Telippalai hospital spokesman said that if the parents had been aware of the rambutan seed stuck in the child's throat, the child's life could have been saved."
      ],
